The paper deals with the Lovasz Local Lemma, which is a fundamental principle in probability theory and has numerous applications in computer science, particularly in graph theory and combinatorics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which is closely related to combinatorics and graph theory. The paper also discusses randomized and deterministic algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of log-space statistical tests indicates a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the focus on graph theory and combinatorics suggests cs.GT (Discrete Mathematics).
